tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE quantum_dataset_metadata (
 id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
 dataset_name STRING,
 dataset_description STRING,
 owner VARCHAR,
 creation_date TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE quantum_dataset_metadata (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    dataset_name VARCHAR(255),
    data_type VARCHAR(50),
    num_samples INT,
    creation_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_workflow (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    workflow_name VARCHAR(255),
    description TEXT,
    created_by VARCHAR(100),
    create_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_data_relationship (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    dataset_id INT,
    workflow_id INT,
    relationship_type VARCHAR(50),
    FOREIGN KEY (dataset_id) REFERENCES quantum_dataset_metadata(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (workflow_id) REFERENCES quantum_workflow(id)
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumDatasets (
    dataset_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    dataset_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    num_qubits INT,
    dataset_size INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumModels (
    model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    model_type VARCHAR(50),
    accuracy FLOAT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumExperiments (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    dataset_id INT,
    model_id INT,
    experiment_status VARCHAR(50),
    started_at TIMESTAMP,
    completed_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumResults (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    result_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    experiment_id INT,
    result_data JSON,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumDatasets (
    dataset_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    dataset_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    dataset_description TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE DatasetFiles (
    file_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    dataset_id UUID,
    file_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    file_size INT NOT NULL,
    file_path TEXT NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE DatasetFeatures (
    feature_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    dataset_id UUID,
    feature_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    feature_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE ModelResults (
    result_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    dataset_id UUID,
    result_metrics JSONB,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);
